# NTS-CLI - The Netflix Test Studio Command Line Interface (NTS-CLI) offers an alternative method for testing your Netflix application.

## Install

```shell script
pip3 install ntscli-client
```

Internal users can leverage the following command to pull builds including internal package extras

```shell script
pip3 install 'ntscli-client[internal]'
```

## Usage

All NTS-CLI commands have --help options to document their usage

```shell script
nts --help
```

# Local Development

## Setup

```shell script
# Create virtual environment
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate

# Install for Netflix internal development (includes all test and dev tools)
pip install -e '.[internal]'

# Or install base CLI only (external user experience)
pip install -e .
```

## Running Tests

```shell script
# Run tests
pytest

# With coverage
pytest --cov
```

## Teardown

To clean up the virtual environment when you're done:

```shell script
# Deactivate the virtual environment
deactivate

# Remove the virtual environment directory
rm -rf .venv
```

